1144
00:57:05,300 --> 00:57:08,300
Regions measurement, it's a summary, text summary.

1145
00:57:09,300 --> 00:57:14,300
The regions measurement follows a clear path, not a shortcut.

1146
00:57:15,579 --> 00:57:18,579
The first step is to define the model.

1147
00:57:20,420 --> 00:57:23,420
We must be clear about what we are measuring

1148
00:57:23,420 --> 00:57:26,420
and which attributes we care about.

1149
00:57:28,150 --> 00:57:31,150
Without this, numbers have no meaning.

1150
00:57:32,150 --> 00:57:35,440
Next, we verify representation.

1151
00:57:36,440 --> 00:57:41,440
The numbers must reflect what we observe in the real world.

1152
00:57:42,440 --> 00:57:47,440
If the numbers contradict reality, the measure is wrong.

1153
00:57:49,269 --> 00:57:53,269
After that, we can use derived measures.

1154
00:57:53,269 --> 00:58:00,269
Derived measures help reveal relationships between attributes,

1155
00:58:01,269 --> 00:58:03,269
not just isolated values.

1156
00:58:06,059 --> 00:58:12,059
Once reliable measures exist, prediction systems become possible.

1157
00:58:14,150 --> 00:58:19,150
Prediction always depends on a model and clear procedures.

1158
00:58:20,340 --> 00:58:24,340
Without both, predictions are guesswork.

1159
00:58:24,340 --> 00:58:30,429
Finally, we must respect the measurement scale.

1160
00:58:31,429 --> 00:58:41,429
Nominal and ordinal data do not allow the same operations as ratio data.

1161
00:58:42,690 --> 00:58:47,690
Using the wrong scale leads to wrong conclusions.

1162
00:58:48,849 --> 00:58:49,849
OK, idea here.

1163
00:58:50,849 --> 00:58:53,849
Measurement is not only about collecting data.

1164
00:58:53,849 --> 00:59:00,360
It's about mapping real-world observations

1165
00:59:01,360 --> 00:59:08,360
in a numerical system that we can understand and trust.

