1173
01:00:05,219 --> 01:00:09,280
In this presentation, from the beginning,

1174
01:00:10,280 --> 01:00:18,139
we introduced a conceptual framework that connected all the slides

1175
01:00:18,139 --> 01:00:20,139
and explained how so they're located.

1176
01:00:20,139 --> 01:00:25,420
And how software measurements moved from intuition

1177
01:00:25,420 --> 01:00:29,420
toward a more religious and scientific approach.

1178
01:00:30,809 --> 01:00:37,809
The main idea was the measurement was not merely about producing numbers,

1179
01:00:37,809 --> 01:00:41,809
but about establishing a meaningful relationship

1180
01:00:41,809 --> 01:00:49,809
between real-world software phenomena and numerical representations.

1181
01:00:49,809 --> 01:00:57,610
These slides emphasized the importance of defining the measurement model first,

1182
01:00:57,610 --> 01:01:01,610
particularly the entity-attribute pair.

1183
01:01:01,610 --> 01:01:04,119
Through several examples,

1184
01:01:04,119 --> 01:01:10,119
these presentations showed that commonly used metrics,

1185
01:01:10,119 --> 01:01:16,119
such as false per-clock or silomatic complexity,

1186
01:01:16,119 --> 01:01:19,119
were only meaningful

1187
01:01:19,119 --> 01:01:26,119
when their assumptions and contexts were clearly defined.

1188
01:01:26,119 --> 01:01:33,119
Otherwise, the same metric could lead to correct conclusions in one case

1189
01:01:33,119 --> 01:01:37,119
and misleading interpretations in another.

1190
01:01:37,119 --> 01:01:46,110
Later, the presentation distinguished between direct and real messages

1191
01:01:46,110 --> 01:01:49,110
and demonstrated

1192
01:01:49,110 --> 01:01:54,110
how derived metrics revealed hidden problems

1193
01:01:54,110 --> 01:01:59,110
that raw counts could not expose.

1194
01:01:59,110 --> 01:02:03,530
It then moved from assessment to prediction,

1195
01:02:03,530 --> 01:02:08,530
where prediction was shown to rely on mathematical models,

1196
01:02:08,530 --> 01:02:12,530
assumptions about future behavior,

1197
01:02:12,530 --> 01:02:17,530
and careful interpretation of uncertainty.

1198
01:02:17,530 --> 01:02:18,530
Finally,

1199
01:02:18,530 --> 01:02:22,530
the presentation introduced measurement scales

1200
01:02:22,530 --> 01:02:24,530
and explained

1201
01:02:24,530 --> 01:02:28,530
why respecting their limitations

1202
01:02:28,530 --> 01:02:34,679
was essential for valid analysis.

1203
01:02:34,679 --> 01:02:36,679
Overall,

1204
01:02:36,679 --> 01:02:38,809
the presentation,

1205
01:02:38,809 --> 01:02:41,159
from the beginning until now,

1206
01:02:41,159 --> 01:02:43,159
demonstrated that

1207
01:02:43,159 --> 01:02:48,159
religious software measurement required

1208
01:02:48,159 --> 01:02:50,159
a structured process,

1209
01:02:50,159 --> 01:02:52,159
defining models,

1210
01:02:52,159 --> 01:02:55,159
validating representations,

1211
01:02:55,159 --> 01:02:58,159
using appropriate measures,

1212
01:02:58,159 --> 01:03:01,289
building prediction systems,

1213
01:03:01,289 --> 01:03:05,289
and respecting measurement scales.

1214
